Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm chunks. Pop on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Roast on the top shelf of your #oven{} until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm pieces. Chop the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees). Pop both on another #tray{} and drizzle with @oil{}. Season with @salt{}, @ground black pepper{} and the @za'atar{1}. Roast on the middle shelf until soft, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the @water for the bulgur{200} into a large #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. Stir in half the @chicken stock powder{1}, the @bulgur wheat{100} and the @baby spinach{125}, bring back to the boil, pop a lid on the #pot{} and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Season the @British turkey steaks{4} with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. When hot, lay the turkey steaks in the pan and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each side. Transfer to the tray with the potato and roast until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. 

> IMPORTANT: The turkey is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. When cooked, transfer to a #cutting board{} and leave to rest, loosely covered in #foil{}.

Return the now empty turkey pan to medium heat. Add the @redcurrant jelly{25}, remaining @chicken stock powder{}, @water{} and bring to the boil, stirring to dissolve the jelly. Simmer until thick and glossy, ~{3-4%minutes} then remove from the heat.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

A few mins before you are ready to serve, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another large frying pan. Add the @chopped kale{100} and garlic and stir-fry until wilted, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Reheat the redcurrant jus if needed (just add a little more water if too thick!). Slice the turkey (one steak per person) and serve the roast potatoes, garlicky kale and turkey drizzled with your redcurrant jus. Enjoy!

== Turkey Grain Bowl ==

Chop up the remaining turkey. Pop in a large #bowl{} with the pepper, broccoli and bulgur. Pick the @mint{1}(roughly chopped) leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Zest and halve the @lemon{1}. Add the mint, lemon zest and a squeeze of juice to the bowl and mix.

Allow to cool then divide between your #containers{} and refrigerate. Reheat in the #microwave{} until piping hot or eat cold. Enjoy!